Thanks! If you want the entire sidebar to disappear (not just collapse to icons) when clicking the menu icon, follow these steps:


---

1. Update sidebar.component.ts

Keep a showSidebar boolean:

import { Component } from '@angular/core';

@Component({
  selector: 'app-sidebar',
  templateUrl: './sidebar.component.html',
  styleUrls: ['./sidebar.component.css']
})
export class SidebarComponent {
  showSidebar = true;
  referenceDataExpanded = false;

  toggleSidebar() {
    this.showSidebar = !this.showSidebar;
  }

  toggleReferenceData() {
    this.referenceDataExpanded = !this.referenceDataExpanded;
  }
}


---

2. Update sidebar.component.html

Wrap the entire sidebar with *ngIf="showSidebar" so it completely disappears:

<button class="toggle-button" (click)="toggleSidebar()">
  <mat-icon>{{ showSidebar ? 'menu_open' : 'menu' }}</mat-icon>
</button>

<div *ngIf="showSidebar" class="sidebar-container">
  <ul class="menu">
    <li>
      <mat-icon>apartment</mat-icon>
      <span>Manage Company</span>
    </li>
    <li>
      <mat-icon>description</mat-icon>
      <span>Recon Master</span>
    </li>
    <li>
      <mat-icon>category</mat-icon>
      <span>Context Type</span>
    </li>

    <li (click)="toggleReferenceData()" class="expandable">
      <mat-icon>inventory_2</mat-icon>
      <span>Reference Data</span>
      <mat-icon>{{ referenceDataExpanded ? 'expand_less' : 'expand_more' }}</mat-icon>
    </li>

    <ul *ngIf="referenceDataExpanded" class="submenu">
      <li>Accounting Period Groups</li>
      <li>Calendars</li>
      <li>Counterparties</li>
      <li>Currencies</li>
      <li>Exchange Rates</li>
      <li>Item Types</li>
      <li>Reason Codes</li>
      <li>Securities</li>
      <li>Tags</li>
    </ul>

    <li>
      <mat-icon>search</mat-icon>
      <span>Audit</span>
    </li>
    <li>
      <mat-icon>list_alt</mat-icon>
      <span>Logs</span>
    </li>
  </ul>
</div>


---

3. Basic CSS (sidebar.component.css)

.sidebar-container {
  width: 250px;
  background-color: #1b3b4b;
  color: white;
  height: 100vh;
  padding: 10px;
}

.toggle-button {
  background: none;
  border: none;
  color: #1b3b4b;
  margin: 10px;
  font-size: 24px;
  cursor: pointer;
}


---

Summary:

Menu icon always visible at top-left.

Sidebar fully disappears on toggle (not even icons shown).

You can adjust placement of the toggle button as needed.


Let me know if you want an animation or transition effect.

Thanks for the clarification! You want to use the menu icon already present in the bottom-bar of your header to completely hide/show the sidebar, not add a new button.

Hereâ€™s how to do it properly:


---

Step 1: Modify Sidebar to Listen to External Toggle

In your sidebar.component.ts:

import { Component, Input } from '@angular/core';

@Component({
  selector: 'app-sidebar',
  templateUrl: './sidebar.component.html',
  styleUrls: ['./sidebar.component.css']
})
export class SidebarComponent {
  @Input() showSidebar = true;

  referenceDataExpanded = false;

  toggleReferenceData() {
    this.referenceDataExpanded = !this.referenceDataExpanded;
  }
}


---

Step 2: Wrap Sidebar with *ngIf Based on showSidebar

In sidebar.component.html, wrap the entire sidebar content:

<div *ngIf="showSidebar" class="sidebar-container">
  <!-- sidebar content here exactly as before -->
</div>


---

Step 3: Emit Toggle From Header (app.component.html / wherever the header is)

In the file where your bottom-bar is located (probably app.component.html), change this:

<!-- Before -->
<button class="icon-btn" (click)="toggleSidebar.emit()">
  <span class="material-icons">menu</span>
</button>

To this (trigger a method):

<button class="icon-btn" (click)="toggleSidebar()">
  <span class="material-icons">menu</span>
</button>


---

Step 4: Control Sidebar Visibility in app.component.ts

import { Component } from '@angular/core';

@Component({
  selector: 'app-root',
  templateUrl: './app.component.html',
  styleUrls: ['./app.component.css']
})
export class AppComponent {
  showSidebar = true;

  toggleSidebar() {
    this.showSidebar = !this.showSidebar;
  }
}


---

Step 5: Bind showSidebar to <app-sidebar>

In app.component.html, pass the showSidebar variable:

<app-sidebar [showSidebar]="showSidebar"></app-sidebar>


---

Now, clicking the menu icon in the header will completely hide or show the entire sidebar component.

Let me know if you also want a smooth slide-out animation!

